Iavan Pijoos, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Six people were injured when a bakkie collided with two other vehicles on the N1 South, near the Allandale off-ramp in Midrand, paramedics said on Tuesday.The bakkie caught fire after the crash, Emer-G-Med spokesperson Max Cohen said. Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said traffic was at a standstill. Paramedics and fire and rescue personnel were on the scene.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.